# GraphQL API

{{ project_name }} exposes a **Strawberry GraphQL** endpoint alongside
{%- if api_style == 'both' %} the REST API{% endif %}, mounted at `/graphql`.

## Quick start

```bash
# Start the development server
task dev

# Open GraphiQL IDE (debug mode only)
open http://localhost:8000/graphql
```

## Architecture

The GraphQL layer follows the same **hexagonal / clean architecture**
used by the REST routes. Resolvers are thin — they delegate to the
**application service** layer and return Strawberry types.

```
ports/graphql/
├── __init__.py          # Package marker
├── context.py           # GraphQLContext (DI, auth, request)
├── dataloaders.py       # DataLoader factories (N+1 prevention)
├── extensions.py        # Schema extensions (depth limiter)
├── mutations.py         # Root Mutation type
├── permissions.py       # IsAuthenticated permission class
├── queries.py           # Root Query type
├── router.py            # ProductionGraphQLRouter (error masking)
├── schema.py            # strawberry.Schema assembly
{%- if use_graphql_subscriptions %}
├── subscriptions.py     # Root Subscription type (WebSocket)
{%- endif %}
└── types.py             # Strawberry object/input types
```

